    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>shredded spring greens</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and add to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the greens to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12 min or until the greens are tender</p>",
